{"slideshow_credits": null, "snippet": "From a viral moment on C-Span to a meeting in the Appalachian foothills....", "abstract": "Op-Ed article by public policy expert Heather C McGhee describes receiving phone call from white man after she, a black woman, had been guest on C-Span show discussing racism; recounts caller confessing to be racist, and his startling request for advice on how to change and connect with Americans he had so long viewed as 'other'; suggests such conversations must be replicated across country, and underscores degree to which acceptance that prejudice exists is precondition for any kind of change in American society.", "section_name": "Opinion", "print_page": "2", "document_type": "article", "byline": {"person": [{"lastname": "MCGHEE", "rank": 1, "firstname": "Heather", "role": "reported", "organization": "", "middlename": "C."}], "original": "By HEATHER C. MCGHEE", "contributor": ""}, "web_url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2016/12/10/opinion/sunday/im-prejudiced-he-said-then-we-kept-talking.html", "lead_paragraph": "From a viral moment on C-Span to a meeting in the Appalachian foothills.", "headline": {"print_headline": "\u2018I\u2019m Prejudiced,\u2019 He Said. Then We Kept Talking.", "main": "\u2018I\u2019m Prejudiced,\u2019 He Said. Then We Kept Talking.", "content_kicker": "Opinion", "kicker": "Opinion"}, "_id": "584c3f3995d0e0392607545a", "word_count": "913", "multimedia": [{"height": 126, "url": "images/2016/12/11/opinion/sunday/11mcghee/11mcghee-thumbWide.jpg", "legacy": {"wideheight": "126", "wide": "images/2016/12/11/opinion/sunday/11mcghee/11mcghee-thumbWide.jpg", "widewidth": "190"}, "subtype": "wide", "width": 190, "type": "image"}, {"height": 406, "url": "images/2016/12/11/opinion/sunday/11mcghee/11mcghee-articleLarge.jpg", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2016/12/11/opinion/sunday/11mcghee/11mcghee-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": "600", "xlargeheight": "406"}, "subtype": "xlarge", "width": 600, "type": "image"}, {"height": 75, "url